		\section{Transforming RMarkdown Files}
		There are two ways to transform RMarkdown Files:
		\item 1. knit
		\item 2. convert\\
		
		The \textit{knitr} functions are already included in the \textit{rmarkdown} package. \textit{knitr} will run each chunk of R code in the document and append the results of the code to the document next to the code chunk.\\
		Transforming the RMarkdown file into a new format is called converting. This will convert the .Rmd file into HTML, PDF or a MS Word file without changing text, code, graphs and formatting from the original file.\\
		It is common to do both these transformations in one step. For creating a report, either use the  use the command \textit{rmarkdown::render()}.


